beer.beer_description: This is a dark, malty brew coupled with big hop flavours reminiscent of blackberry and tropical fruits. As the name suggests it pours a deep red colour. The rye kicks up some spicy notes which meld nicely with the malt backbone and fruity hop profile. The body is big enough you know it’s there, but not overwhelmingly chewy, making it drinkable enough to sink a few.
